genresAdvancedInfo.name: romanian classical piano
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Romanian classical piano music is a genre of music that originated in Romania and is characterized by its use of piano as the primary instrument. It is often associated with the works of composers such as George Enescu and Dinu Lipatti. The music is typically complex and intricate, featuring a wide range of emotions and moods.
